claim.claim-text:
15. A method of forming a compression sleeve for being wrapped around a leg of a wearer, the method comprising:
securing two layers of flexible material together to at least partially define first and second adjacent flexible sections, the securing of said two layers of flexible material comprising securing two bladder layers together to define a first inflatable bladder and a second inflatable bladder disposed more proximally than the first inflatable bladder when the sleeve is wrapped around the leg, the first bladder forming at least a part of the first flexible sleeve section and the second bladder forming at least a part of the second flexible sleeve section;
securing a structural component to the sleeve such that the structural component extends generally between the first and second adjacent flexible sections to maintain a spacing between the sleeve sections lengthwise of the leg when the sleeve is wrapped around the leg;
said securing two layers of flexible material together further forming a connecting section defining a knee opening for being located at a knee of the wearer, the connecting section defining bridge members disposed on opposite sides of the knee opening between the adjacent flexible sleeve sections, the structural component extending through one of the bridge members; and
joining the bladder layers together at a first pair of spot welds on opposite sides of the structural component at a first location and at a second pair of spot welds on opposite sides of the structural component at a second location spaced from the first location to locate the structural component on the sleeve so as to maintain the spacing of the adjacent sleeve sections.
